ull,{"children":"Ledger board repair & proper flashing"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Rotting joist & rim board replacement"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Railing post & stair safety upgrades"}]]}],["$","li","3",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Full deck resurfacing (wood or composite)"}]]}],["$","li","4",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Loudoun County permit management"}]]}],["$","li","5",{"children":[["$","svg",null,{"width":"20","height":"20","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"3","strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","children":["$","polyline",null,{"points":"20 6 9 17 4 12"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Free on-site estimates - call (571) 655-7207"}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}]
1e:["$","section",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__section","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__container","children":[["$","div","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__textBlock","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__subTitle","children":"Loudoun County's Trusted Deck Repair Contractor"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"$undefined","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Loudoun County is one of the fastest-growing and most prosperous counties in the United States - and its homeowners expect a high standard when it comes to maintaining their properties. Decks in Loudoun County face a unique combination of environmental stressors: the high humidity and intense summer heat of Northern Virginia, followed by freeze-thaw cycles that expand and contract wood and concrete year after year. Loudoun Decks has spent years repairing and restoring decks in Ashburn, Leesburg, Sterling, Brambleton, and across the county - and we understand exactly what Loudoun homes need."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Many Loudoun County decks were built in the construction boom of the 2000s and early 2010s, using pressure-treated lumber and builder-grade fasteners that are now approaching the end of their effective lifespan. These decks may look fine on the surface, but hidden rot in the ledger board, subframe joists, and post bases is extremely common. Our team performs thorough substructure inspections - crawling under the deck to check every joist, beam, and connection point - before providing a repair proposal."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["If you are a Loudoun County homeowner searching for a deck contractor near you who combines local expertise with the highest standards of craftsmanship, Loudoun Decks is the team to call. We are 5-Star Google Rated, fully licensed and insured, and have completed hundreds of repairs throughout the county."]}]]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__textBlock","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__subTitle","children":"Common Deck Repair Issues in Loudoun County Homes"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"$undefined","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["The single most dangerous deck failure point - and the most common issue we encounter in Loudoun County - is the ledger board connection. The ledger board is the structural member that bolts your deck to the house's rim joist. When this connection fails due to rot, inadequate fastening, or missing flashing, the deck can collapse. In Loudoun County, we frequently find ledger boards on older decks that were nailed rather than through-bolted, or that lack proper flashing to prevent water infiltration. Repairing and properly flashing the ledger is one of the most critical safety upgrades we perform."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Railing instability is the second most common repair request from Loudoun County homeowners. Virginia building codes require deck railings to withstand 200 lbs of lateral force at the top rail - a standard that many older railings simply cannot meet. Railing posts that are face-mounted to the outer rim joist rather than through-bolted to the framing are particularly vulnerable. We upgrade railing post connections throughout Ashburn, Leesburg, and Sterling to meet or exceed current Loudoun County building code requirements."]}],"$L30"]}],"$L31"]}],"$L32","$L33"]}]}]
